Step 1 : Create a base template
{% load static %}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lamg="en">
<head>
    <meta chardet="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width-device-width, initial-sclae=1.0">
    <title>{% block title %}Restaurant{% endblock %}</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="{% static 'css/style.css' %}">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Our Restaurant</h1>
    </header>

    <main>
       {% block content %}{% endblock %}
    </main>

    <footer style="text-align: center; margin-top: 20px; padding: 10px; background: #f4f4f4;">
       Powered by Django
    </footer>
</body>
</html>


Step 2 : Extend the base template in your pages
{% extends "base.html" %}

{% block title %}Home - Restaurant{% endblock %}
 
{% block content %}
    <h2>Welcome to Our Restaurant</h2>
    <p>Enjoy delicious meals and a grate ambiance.</p>
{% endblock %}


Step 3 : Result
1. Every page that extends base.html will now automatically have "Powered by Django" in the footer.
2 You only need to change the footer in one file if you ever want to update it. 